* * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *

SYNOPSIS
  demo [OPTION...]

DESCRIPTION
  Procedurally generate 2D maps using the wave function collapse algorithm.

OPTIONS
  Functional
    -d, --debug
      Output is extra verbose and will provide logs.

    -f, --fps
      Display the amount of frames per second being displayed.

    -h, --help
      Print out this menu to stdout.

    --grid-size
      Change the length of the tiles in the grid. 

  Cosemetic
    --background-color=HEXCOLOR
      Makes the background color the six digit hexidecimal value given.

    --grid-color=HEXCOLOR
      Makes the grid and number color the six digit hexidecimal value given.

    -n
      Display numbers on tiles representing the amount of tiles possible. 
